verses.text: \f + \fr 130:1 \fqa Alex. \ft + 'for David.'\f*A Song of Degrees. O Lord, my heart is not exalted, neither have mine eyes been \add haughtily\add* raised: neither have I exercised myself in great \add matters\add*, nor in things too wonderful for me.
\add I shall have sinned\add* if I have not been humble, but have exalted my soul: according to \add the relation of\add* a weaned child to his mother, so wilt thou recompense my soul.
Let Israel hope in the Lord, from henceforth and for ever.
